This Next.js project follows a modern app directory structure with specific conventions:

## Key Directories

- `src/app/`: Main application routes and page components
  - `(index)/`: Home page and related components
  - `docs/`: Documentation pages and related components
    - `[[...slug]]/`: Dynamic documentation routes
    - `@aside/`: Parallel route for documentation sidebar
    - `@nav/`: Parallel route for documentation navigation

- `src/components/`: Reusable components
  - `layout/`: Layout-specific components
  - `ui/`: UI components and primitives

- `src/lib/`: Utility functions and shared code
  - `css/`: CSS utilities and helpers
  - `types/`: TypeScript type definitions

- `content/`: Documentation content
  - `docs/`: Markdown/MDX documentation files

## Conventions

1. All React components should be TypeScript files (.tsx)
2. Use Next.js 13+ App Router conventions
3. Follow parallel routes pattern for complex layouts
4. Keep components modular and reusable
5. Maintain clear separation between UI components and business logic
